checkSignatures(bytes32,bytes,bytes).details: Checks whether the signature provided is valid for the provided data, hash. Will revert otherwise.

params.dataHash: Hash of the data (could be either a message hash or transaction hash)
params.signatures: Signature data that should be verified. Can be ECDSA signature, contract signature (EIP-1271) or approved hash.

disableModule(address,address).details: Allows to remove a module from the whitelist.      This can only be done via a Safe transaction.

params.prevModule: Module that pointed to the module to be removed in the linked list

enableModule(address).details: Allows to add a module to the whitelist.      This can only be done via a Safe transaction.

encodeTransactionData((address,uint256,b.details: Returns the bytes that are hashed to be signed by owner.

execTransaction((address,uint256,bytes,u.details: Allows to execute a Safe transaction confirmed by required number of owners and then pays the account that submitted the transaction. Note: The fees are always transferred, even if the user transaction fails.

params.signatures: Packed signature data ({bytes32 r}{bytes32 s}{uint8 v})

execTransactionFromModule(address,uint25.details: Allows a Module to execute a Safe transaction without any further confirmations.

execTransactionFromModuleReturnData(addr.details: Allows a Module to execute a Safe transaction without any further confirmations and return data

getChainId().details: Returns the chain id used by this contract.

getModulesPaginated(address,uint256).details: Returns array of modules. Useful for a widget

params.pageSize: Maximum number of modules that should be returned.

getNonce(uint256).details: returns a value from the nonces 2d mapping

params.batchId: : the key of the user's batch being queried

returns._0: nonce : the number of transaction made within said batch

getTransactionHash(address,uint256,bytes.details: Returns hash to be signed by owner.

params.baseGas: Gas costs for data used to trigger the safe transaction.
params.gasPrice: Maximum gas price that should be used for this transaction.
params.gasToken: Token address (or 0 if ETH) that is used for the payment.
params.refundReceiver: Address of receiver of gas payment (or 0 if tx.origin).
params.targetTxGas: Fas that should be used for the safe transaction.

isModuleEnabled(address).details: Returns if an module is enabled

returns._0: True if the module is enabled

requiredTxGas(address,uint256,bytes,uint.details: Allows to estimate a transaction.      This method is only meant for estimation purpose, therefore the call will always revert and encode the result in the revert data.      Since the `estimateGas` function includes refunds, call this method to get an estimated of the costs that are deducted from the safe with `execTransaction`

returns._0: Estimate without refunds and overhead fees (base transaction and payload data gas costs).

setFallbackHandler(address).details: Allows to add a contract to handle fallback calls.      Only fallback calls without value and with data will be forwarded.      This can only be done via a Safe transaction.

params.interfaceId: The interface identifier, as specified in ERC165

validateUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,by.details: Must validate caller is the entryPoint.      Must validate the signature and nonce

params.requestId: hash of the user's request data. can be used as the basis for signature.
params.requiredPrefund: the minimum amount to transfer to the sender(entryPoint) to be able to make the call.      The excess is left as a deposit in the entrypoint, for future calls.      can be withdrawn anytime using "entryPoint.withdrawTo()"      In case there is a paymaster in the request (or the current deposit is high enough), this value will be zero.
params.userOp: the operation that is about to be executed.

disableModule(address,address).notice: Disables the module `module` for the Safe.

enableModule(address).notice: Enables the module `module` for the Safe.

requiredTxGas(address,uint256,bytes,uint.notice: review necessity for this method for estimating execute call

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Query if a contract implements an interface

updateImplementation(address).notice: Updates the implementation of the base wallet

validateUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,by.notice: Validate user's signature and nonce the entryPoint will make the call to the recipient only if this validation call returns successfuly.
